  ./COVERAGE.md:957:| `org.apache.pekko:pekko-actor_2.13` | [1.1.5<br>- 1.6.0](metadata/org.apache.pekko/pekko-actor_2.13/index.json) | <details><summary>Show</summary> Apache Pekko Actor provides the core actor-system runtime for building concurrent, distributed, resilient message-driven JVM applications in Java and Scala. It includes the classic actor APIs, dispatching, supervision, routing, scheduling, event streams, configuration integration, and foundational utilities used by other Pekko modules.</details> | [77.3% (34/44 calls)](stats/org.apache.pekko/pekko-actor_2.13/) |
  ./COVERAGE.md:958:| `org.apache.pekko:pekko-parsing_2.13` | [1.3.0](metadata/org.apache.pekko/pekko-parsing_2.13/index.json) | <details><summary>Show</summary> Apache Pekko Parsing is a Scala-specific internal support module for Pekko HTTP that provides compile-time logging guards and cross-Scala-version compatibility annotations used by the HTTP parsing implementation. It is published as a JVM JAR for each Scala binary version, including Scala 2.13, so downstream Pekko HTTP modules can share those internal helpers without duplicating them.</details> | [100.0% (0/0 calls)](stats/org.apache.pekko/pekko-parsing_2.13/) |
