ttp.shared/pekko_3/1.5.1/execution-metrics.json:46:      \"summary\": \"The library's only meaningful API is Pekko-stream based, but `org.apache.pekko:pekko-stream_3:1.5.0` is declared as `provided` in the artifact POM and is not pulled transitively for tests.\",\n./stats/com.softwaremill.sttp.shared/pekko_3/1.5.1/execution-metrics.json:52:          \"reason\": \"`sttp.capabilities.pekko.PekkoStreams` exposes and calls `org.apache.pekko.stream.scaladsl.Source`, `FlowOps`, and `org.apache.pekko.util.ByteString`; the upstream build marks `pekko-stream` as provided, so generated tests need it explicitly to compile and exercise the API.\"\n./stats/com.softwaremill.sttp.shared/pekko_3/1.5.1/execution-metrics.json:55:      \"agent_guidance\": \"For meaningful coverage, create a small Pekko `Source` of `ByteString`, call `PekkoStreams.limitBytes`, materialize it using a short-lived `org.apache.pekko.actor.ActorSystem`, and terminate the actor system after the assertion. No Docker image, environment variable, or system property appears required.\",\n./stats/com.softwaremill.sttp.shared/pekko_3/1.5.1/execution-metrics.json:57:        \"The artifact is a Scala 3 module, so generated Java tests may need to use the Java-accessible forms of Scala/Pekko APIs carefully.\",\n./stats/com.softwaremill.sttp.shared/pekko_3/1.5.1/execution-metrics.json:58:        \"Pekko stream materialization may introduce native-image metadata needs, but local Gradle and Native Image verification should remain authoritative.\"\n./stats/com.softwaremill.sttp.shared/pekko_3/1.5.1/execution-metrics.json:97:      \"test_file\": \"tests/src/com.softwaremill.sttp.shared/pekko_3/1.5.1/src/test/scala/com_softwaremill_sttp_shared/pekko_3/Pekko_3Test.scala\",\n./stats/io.scalaland/chimney_3/2.0.0-M1/stats.json:3:    \"version\" : \"2.0.0-M1\",\n./stats/io.scalaland/chimney_3/2.0.0-M1/execution-metrics.json:4:    \"library\": \"io.scalaland:chimney_3:2.0.0-M1\",\n./stats/io.scalaland/chimney_3/2.0.0-M1/execution